%N A076964 a(1) = 3, then a(n) = smallest multiple of the previous term with as many divisors.
%C A076964 If the first conjecture in A262981 from _Vladimir Letsko_ is true, then this is also: a(2) = 9, thereafter a(n+1) = least k with a(n) divisors. - _Jianing Song_, May 31 2026
%e A076964 a(2) = 9 tau(9) = 3, a(3) = 36 tau(36) = 9 etc.
